  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Development of a Regional Science, Technology and Innovation Database for evidenced-based policies in Eastern Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">EASTECO in collaboration with key stakeholders including UNESCO developed the EAC Regional STI Policy for adoption by Member States. However, the lack of reliable up-to-date data and indicators on the current status of STI at the country-level may hamper the realisation of the policy&apos;s objectives and expected outcomes. The establishment of national and regional STI baselines that enable the monitoring of STI indicators and the support for learning and policy decisions at multiple scales is the mainstream opportunity. UNESCO&apos;s GO-SPIN methodology offers the platform to address these gaps. In collaboration with multiple stakeholders, this project will develop a comprehensive regional STI database for evidenced-based STI policy decisions in the EAC.</narrative>
  </description>
